Activity: A9 - Discover privacy technique used online

Objective
The goal of this activity was to investigate how websites and online services protect users' personal information and maintain privacy while browing or using online platforms

Method
I visited several popular websites and online services and checked their privacy features. i examined how they handle user data, protect communication, and give users control over what information is shared.

Findings
The websites and online services I analysed use the following privacy techniques:
1. Cookie consent banners - websites ask for permission before storing tracking cookies, giving users control over what data is collected
2. Private browsing modes - browsers like chrome and safari offer incognito/private browsing mode, which does not save history, cookies, or temporary files

Security Principle
These privacy techniques support confidentiality and integrity by protecting user data from unauthorised access and ensuring it is only shared according to the user's preference

Reflection
This activity showed me how privacy techniques are implemented online and how they protect users in everyday internet use. It highlighted that privacy is not just about passwords—it also involves encryption, user consent, and account controls.
